If a merchant changes the property price from 80L → 75L, how does Elasticsearch get updated? Direct synchronous call? Event/queue? Or something else?

PostgreSQL is the source of truth. We use CDC to keep Elasticsearch synchronized.

Merchant updates property
       ↓
Property Service
       ↓
Postgres (commit)
       ↓
CDC reads WAL
       ↓
Kafka/Event Stream
       ↓
Search Indexer
       ↓
Elasticsearch updated


Why CDC instead of directly updating Elasticsearch?


CDC helps because:

DB commit happens first.
WAL becomes the source of truth.
Failed indexing can be retried.
Rebuilding Elasticsearch becomes easier.




Don't say:

We send DB updates as events to Elasticsearch.

because technically the database is not sending events.

More accurately:

CDC tool (e.g. Debezium)
    ↓
Reads WAL/binlog
    ↓
Produces events
    ↓
Consumers update Elasticsearch

