This is where I'd challenge you.

Suppose users search:

3BHK Hyderabad under 80L

Can we cache it?

Yes.

But then:

3BHK Hyderabad under 75L
3BHK Hyderabad under 70L
2BHK Hyderabad
...

Search combinations explode.

So I'd ask:

Is caching search results worth it?

Usually Elasticsearch itself is already optimized for search, so many designs cache only the hottest queries.




