How do we make sure there won't be double booking (contention management)

1. Optimistic locking in Postgres to prevent double booking.

optimistic lock on db on property 123 
Update Status as reserved  -> with expiry as well, 
Remove lock
Then go ahead with the payment 
Then lock again and update status to booked.


2.  I proposed splitting the payment flow into two APIs:
POST /reserve (hold for 5 mins)  
POST /confirm (after successful payment)

And used a distributed lock (Redis) to manage contention.




If payemnt failed then -> lock expires


Run some cron job: 

UPDATE property
SET status='AVAILABLE'
WHERE status='RESERVED'
  AND expires_at < NOW();

Can we narrow the scan?



But during heavy traffic this may cause the DB overload

SOl : Indexing

status = RESERVED
will be a tiny subset of all properties.

And with an index on:

(status, expires_at)
the DB can efficiently find only expired reservations.



index updates are tiny compared to DB scans so uodating indexes is better.


